        <p class="text-sm opacity-40 mb-10 italic">Last updated: February 2026</p>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <div class="highlight-box">
                <h2 class="!border-l-0 !pl-0 !mb-4 text-xl">Shurp Rules:
                    TL;DR</h2>
                <p class="mb-4 opacity-100">Before you hit the road, remember:</p>
                <ul class="compact-list text-sm md:text-base opacity-100">
                    <li><strong>Shurp is not a taxi.</strong> It's a platform where people share available seats.
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Cost sharing.</strong> Trips are not a commercial service.</li>
                    <li><strong>No fees.</strong> Shurp doesn't charge for using the platform.</li>
                    <li><strong>Be responsible.</strong> If plans change — let others know (no ghosting).</li>
                    <li><strong>Your car – Your rules.</strong> Agree on pets and luggage before the trip.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>1. What is Shurp?</h2>
            <p>Shurp is a technology platform that connects private individuals (drivers and passengers) heading the
                same way to share trip costs.</p>
            <p>Shurp <strong class="opacity-100 text-[#1F2933] font-semibold">does not provide</strong> transportation
                services, does not manage vehicles, does not
                employ drivers, and does not offer taxi or courier services.</p>
            <p>When users agree on a trip, obligations arise directly between the driver and passenger.
                Shurp is not a party to this agreement and only provides a technical platform for communication and
                cost calculation.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>2. Participant Requirements</h2>
            <p>To use the platform, you must be at least <strong class="opacity-100 text-[#1F2933] font-semibold">18
                    years old</strong>.</p>
            <ul class="compact-list">
                <li><strong class="opacity-100 text-[#1F2933] font-semibold">Drivers:</strong> Valid driver's license,
                    valid MTPL insurance, and vehicle in proper
                    technical condition.</li>
                <li><strong class="opacity-100 text-[#1F2933] font-semibold">Passengers:</strong> Trips must be booked
                    in your own name. You cannot reserve a seat
                    for minors without an accompanying adult.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-sm opacity-50 mt-4 italic">Shurp reserves the right to request additional
                information or suspend an account if there are doubts about compliance with these terms.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>3. Cost Sharing Principle</h2>
            <p>Shurp is based on fair cost distribution.</p>
            <ul class="compact-list">
                <li>Latvian regulations state that drivers cannot profit from trips.</li>
                <li>The platform's algorithm sets the maximum cost coverage amount.</li>
                <li>Users agree on payments between themselves.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="mt-4 p-4 border-l-2 border-[#125E8A]/30 bg-[#E6F1F7]">
                <p class="text-sm"><strong class="opacity-100 text-[#1F2933] font-semibold">Important:</strong> Shurp
                    does not process payments, does not maintain
                    financial accounts, and does not charge commission fees. Users are responsible for their own tax
                    and financial obligations.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>4. Safety and Liability</h2>
            <ul class="compact-list">
                <li>Private MTPL covers passengers if the trip is non-commercial.</li>
                <li>The driver has the right to verify the passenger's identity before the trip.</li>
                <li>Users are responsible for their own actions, safety, and belongings.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-6 mb-2"><strong class="opacity-100 text-[#1F2933] font-semibold">Liability Limitation:</strong>
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm">Shurp is not responsible for traffic accidents, user actions, losses during trips, or
                disputes between users. The platform is provided "as-is".</p>
            <p class="text-sm">To the extent permitted by law, Shurp's total liability in any case does not exceed
                <strong class="opacity-100 text-[#1F2933] font-semibold">0 EUR</strong>, as the platform does not charge
                for services.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>5. Account Suspension</h2>
            <p>Shurp reserves the right to suspend or delete a user account at any time if these terms, regulations,
                or other users' safety are violated.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>6. Community Guidelines</h2>
            <ul class="compact-list">
                <li>If you're running late or can't make it — inform the other party.</li>
                <li>Repeated no-shows (ghosting) may affect your rating or platform access.</li>
                <li>For inappropriate behavior, use the <strong
                        class="opacity-100 text-[#1F2933] font-semibold">"Report"</strong> function.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>7. Data Protection</h2>
            <p>Personal data processing is carried out in accordance with Shurp's Privacy Policy. You can request
                deletion of your data by writing to <span id="safe-email-info-section"></span>.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>8. Dispute Resolution</h2>
            <p>Latvian law applies. Disputes are primarily resolved through negotiation or in Latvian courts
                according to jurisdiction.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-section">
            <div class="legal-footer-box">
                <p class="opacity-100 mb-4"><strong class="opacity-100 text-[#1F2933] font-semibold">9. Legal
                        Information</strong></p>
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                    <div>
                        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40 mb-1">Service Provider</p>
                        <p class="font-bold">SIA Shurp</p>
                        <p class="text-sm opacity-60">Reg. No. LV40203709369</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40 mb-1">Legal Address</p>
                        <p class="text-sm">Briežu iela 9, Lapsas, LV-2107, Latvia</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="pt-4 border-t border-[#E2E8F0]">
                        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40 mb-1">DSA Contact Point</p>
                        <span id="safe-email-legal"></span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="pt-4 border-t border-[#E2E8F0]">
                        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest opacity-40 mb-1">General Inquiries</p>
                        <span id="safe-email-info-footer"></span>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <p class="mt-6 text-xs opacity-40">Shurp platform operations are supervised by Latvian competent
